23/05/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Partizan Belgrade football club leader Milos Radisavljevic was arrested on suspicion of threatening popular journalist Brankica Stankovic, B92 reported on Friday (May 21st).
He was detained over a December 2009 incident when thousands chanted threats and insults against the B92 reporter during a football match.
Stankovic has received numerous threats after reporting on fans suspected of hooligan attacks.
(Beta, Tanjug - 22/05/10;
B92, Radio Free Europe - 21/05/10)
